messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Endpoint path
- /api/products

All methods acceptable?
- false

Method support (based on code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- server.js mounts the product router at the /api/products prefix: app.use('/api/products', productRoutes);
- In routes/productRoutes.js the route for the router root path ('/') is defined as:
  - router.route('/').get(getProducts).post(protect, admin, createProduct);
  This means the full path is /api/products and the code registers handlers for GET and POST on that path.
- GET: true because getProducts is explicitly registered for the path '/' on the router, resulting in GET /api/products.
- POST: true because createProduct is explicitly registered for the same route (POST /api/products); note it is protected by middleware (protect, admin) but the route exists in the code.
- PUT, DELETE, PATCH: false because those methods are only registered on '/:id' (e.g., PUT /api/products/:id, DELETE /api/products/:id) and not on '/'.
- HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE: false because there are no explicit handlers for these methods in the code for the /api/products path. (Although Express can implicitly handle HEAD by delegating to GET at runtime, the instructions required basing acceptance only on the code, not on runtime/behavioral assumptions.)
- "All methods" is false because not every HTTP method is registered for this path in the source code.
